A vintage 1970s-style film editing room with warm amber lighting, featuring an old Steenbeck flatbed film editor with reels of 35mm film cascading across a wooden desk. Scattered film strips curl organically around the workspace, some hanging from clothespins on a wire above. A pair of worn leather editing gloves rest beside scissors and a splicing block. Through a dusty window, golden afternoon sunlight streams in, illuminating floating dust particles and creating lens flares across the scene. The color palette emphasizes burnt oranges, deep browns, and faded yellows, with film grain texture overlay giving the entire image an authentic retro documentary feel.
